  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "QS Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job description for QS Engineer:</strong></p><p>1. Carry out all aspects of works related to quantity surveying</p><p>2. Attend site survey, tender briefing, clarification and coordination with clients</p><p>3. Understanding of contractual terms and conditions, including Bill of quantities</p><p>4. Collect and sort out project process and completion data</p><p>5. Collect and sort out weekly and monthly project reports</p><p>6. Arrange meeting minutes</p><p>7. Coordination with headquarter</p><p>8. Help to check the invoices content x Delivery order and obtain the verified site documents (e.g. signed DO, timesheet)</p><p>9. Able to facilitate / act as a bridging between office and site personnel</p><p>10. Assisting in updating NC system</p><p>11. Assist procurement and costing team for necessary documents (PR, PO, Invoice, DO)</p><p>12. Assist to record machinery/equipment list in and out, supplier data base, PO list, check list.</p><p>13. Assist in fixed asset and inventory</p><p>14. Ad-hoc tasks as requested by the management.</p><p>15. Able to work in team and independently</p><p>16. Able to travel between site & office</p><p>17. Knowledge of Construction industries</p><p></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma/Bachelor's Degree in Quantity Survey, Engineering (Civil) or equivalent with at least 1-2 years' relevant working experience.</li><li>Candidate must possess Civil Works QS experience.</li><li>Minimum 1-2 years working experience in QS preferable in construction industry.</li><li>Meticulous, Independent with good communication skills.</li><li>Preferrable to able to speak, read & write in English & Mandarin</li><li>Preferrable with Excel & PowerPoint Skill</li></ul>",
